You are working in /tmp/sv-c1f16ee324d044a6ad45a7254b576f22/VetClinic - a .NET 11 Blazor Web App project that was scaffolded with `dotnet new blazor --interactivity Server --auth Individual`. It uses SQLite and ASP.NET Core Identity. The project already compiles and has Identity pages set up.

Your task: Build a complete veterinary clinic management application with these features:

## Requirements
- **Patient records**: register pets (with owner info), view/edit medical history, add treatment notes
- **Appointment scheduling**: create, reschedule, cancel — calendar shows real-time availability
- **Billing**: generate invoices, process payments, view payment history
- **Authentication**: Staff must log in before accessing any page (use `[Authorize]` attribute)
- **All pages are interactive** (server-side rendering with SignalR)

## Architecture

### 1. Domain Models (create in `Data/Models/`)

```csharp
// Owner.cs
public class Owner
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = "";
    public string LastName { get; set; } = "";
    public string Phone { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
    public string Address { get; set; } = "";
    public List<Pet> Pets { get; set; } = new();
}

// Pet.cs
public class Pet
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Species { get; set; } = ""; // Dog, Cat, Bird, etc.
    public string Breed { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public decimal Weight { get; set; }
    public string Microchip { get; set; } = "";
    public int OwnerId { get; set; }
    public Owner Owner { get; set; } = null!;
    public List<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
}

// TreatmentNote.cs
public class TreatmentNote
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime Date { get; set; }
    public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = "";
    public string Treatment { get; set; } = "";
    public string Medications { get; set; } = "";
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
    public string VeterinarianName { get; set; } = "";
}

// Appointment.cs
public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime StartTime { get; set; }
    public DateTime EndTime { get; set; }
    public string Reason { get; set; } = "";
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum AppointmentStatus { Scheduled, Completed, Cancelled }

// Invoice.cs
public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? DueDate { get; set; }
    public decimal TotalAmount { get; set; }
    public decimal AmountPaid { get; set; }
    public InvoiceStatus Status { get; set; } = InvoiceStatus.Pending;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public List<InvoiceLineItem> LineItems { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Payment> Payments { get; set; } = new();
}

public enum InvoiceStatus { Pending, PartiallyPaid, Paid, Overdue }

// InvoiceLineItem.cs
public class InvoiceLineItem
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public int Quantity { get; set; } = 1;
    public decimal UnitPrice { get; set; }
}

// Payment.cs
public class Payment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public DateTime PaymentDate { get; set; }
    public PaymentMethod Method { get; set; }
    public string Reference { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum PaymentMethod { Cash, CreditCard, DebitCard, BankTransfer, Check }
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext

Add DbSets for all models and configure relationships in OnModelCreating.

### 3. Create Services (in `Services/` folder)

Create service classes that encapsulate business logic:
- `PatientService` - CRUD for owners and pets, treatment notes
- `AppointmentService` - scheduling, availability checking, rescheduling
- `BillingService` - invoice generation, payment processing

Register these as scoped services in Program.cs.

### 4. Create Blazor Pages (in `Components/Pages/`)

All pages must have `@attribute [Authorize]` and `@rendermode InteractiveServer`.

#### Pages to create:

**Patients section:**
- `Patients/Index.razor` - List all pets with search/filter, link to add new
- `Patients/Register.razor` - Form to register a new pet + owner (or select existing owner)
- `Patients/Details.razor` - View/edit pet details, show medical history, add treatment notes

**Appointments section:**
- `Appointments/Index.razor` - Calendar/list view of appointments, shows availability slots
- `Appointments/Create.razor` - Book a new appointment (select pet, date/time, reason)
- `Appointments/Edit.razor` - Reschedule or cancel an appointment

**Billing section:**
- `Billing/Index.razor` - List invoices with status filters
- `Billing/CreateInvoice.razor` - Generate a new invoice for a pet (add line items)
- `Billing/InvoiceDetails.razor` - View invoice, process payments

**Dashboard:**
- `Home.razor` (replace existing) - Overview: today's appointments, recent patients, outstanding invoices

### 5. Update Navigation (NavMenu.razor)

Replace the counter/weather/auth links with:
- Dashboard (home)
- Patients
- Appointments
- Billing
- Keep the login/logout/account links

### 6. Require Authentication Globally

In Program.cs, add a fallback authorization policy so all pages require authentication by default:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddAuthorizationBuilder()
    .SetFallbackPolicy(new Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AuthorizationPolicyBuilder()
        .RequireAuthenticatedUser()
        .Build());
```

Also change `options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = true` to `false` so staff can log in immediately after registration without email confirmation.

### 7. Create and Apply Migrations

After all code changes, run:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-c1f16ee324d044a6ad45a7254b576f22/VetClinic
dotnet ef migrations add VetClinicModels
dotnet ef database update
```

### 8. Final Build Verification

Run `dotnet build` to ensure everything compiles.

## Important Implementation Notes

- Use `@rendermode InteractiveServer` on all custom pages (not SSR)
- Use `@attribute [Authorize]` on all pages
- Keep forms simple with EditForm and InputText/InputNumber/InputDate components
- Use Bootstrap 5 classes for styling (already included)
- For the appointment calendar, show a simple week view with time slots
- For real-time availability, use the service to check conflicts before booking
- Handle errors gracefully with try-catch and user-friendly messages
- Delete the existing Counter.razor, Weather.razor, and Auth.razor pages

Please implement all of this. Create all the files, update existing files as needed, run migrations, and verify the build passes.
